H2: GENERAL-PROVISIONS-INCHOATE-CRIMES  
7.432: CHINA CLAIMS Articles22(PREPARATION) ∧23(ATTEMPT);  
  APPLY→IP-INFRINGING CRIMES;  
  TRIGGER CRIMINAL-PROSECUTION ∧ PENALTIES [CHN-WS:35-37].  
7.433: US REPLIES: THRESHOLDS RULE OUT CRIMINAL-LIABILITY;  
  BASED ON ACTUAL-INFRINGEMENT EVIDENCE [US-ORAL2:34].  
7.433.1: US NOTES: Criminal-Law ∧ Judicial-Interp19(2004)/6(2007);  
  NO PREPARATION/ATTEMPT PROVISIONS FOR TRADEMARK-COUNTERFEITING ∧ COPYRIGHT-PIRACY [US-Q8].  
7.434: PANEL OBSERVES Part1,ChII,Sec2 DEFINES INCHOATE-CRIMES=PREPARATION ∧ ATTEMPT ∧ DISCONTINUATION.  
DEF: PREPARATION FOR A CRIME=PREPARE-INSTRUMENTS ∨ CREATE-CONDITIONS FOR CRIME;  
  OFFENDER PREPARATION→LIGHTER/MITIGATED-PUNISHMENT ∨ EXEMPTION [CHN-EXH1].  
7.435: DEF: CRIMINAL-ATTEMPT=OFFENDER STARTS CRIME ∧ PREVENTED-FROM-COMPLETION ∵ INDEPENDENT-OF-WILL;  
  ATTEMPTER→LIGHTER/MITIGATED-PUNISHMENT [CHN-EXH1].  
7.436: PANEL NOTES: Articles22/23 APPLY GENERALLY TO “A-CRIME”(犯罪) ∧ NO EXPRESS LIMITATION;  
  LOCATED Part1,ChI(General-Provisions) ∧ ChIII-IV(Punishments).  
7.436.1: NO TEXTUAL BASIS TO EXCLUDE IP-CRIMES(Arts213/214/215/217/218);  
  JUDICIAL-DECISIONS SHOW COURTS APPLYING Articles22/23 IN IP-INFRINGING CASES [CHN-JUD-EX].  
7.437: PANEL NOTES: CHINA USES PREPARATION/ATTEMPT TO INCLUDE PACKAGING ∧ PRODUCT-COMPONENTS;  
  CHINA DOES NOT ALLEGE BROADENED SCOPE BELOW-THRESHOLDS(Arts213–220).  

H2: GENERAL-PROVISIONS-JOINT-CRIMES  
7.438: JAPAN ∧ EC ARGS: QUANTITATIVE-THRESHOLDS FAIL TO CAPTURE COMMERCIAL-SCALE COUNTERFEITING;  
  WHEN VALUE/QUANTITY LIMITED ∧ PROFESSIONAL-ORG ∧ SYSTEMATIC-COOPERATION [JPN3RD:17; EC-ORAL:10].  
7.438.1: MEXICO STATES: SMALL-SCALE ACTIVITY CLEARLY-MEANINGFUL ∵ CONTRIBUTES TO INFRINGEMENT-CHAIN [MEX-ORAL:6-7].  
7.439: CHINA REFERS Arts25/26/27(CRIMINAL-LAW);  
  FEATURES: JOINT-LIABILITY ∧ CRIMINAL-GROUPS ∧ ACCOMPLICES;  
  CAPTURES NON-QUANTITATIVE-FACTORS(EVIDENCE-COLLABORATION);  
  APPLY→IP-INFRINGING-CRIMES(Arts213/214/215/217/218) [CHN-WS].  
7.440: US REPLIES: NO CONSEQUENCE FOR SOLO-INFRINGERS;  
  EVIDENCE ONLY CAPTURES BELOW-THRESHOLD ACTIVITY IF PART OF ABOVE-THRESHOLD ACTIVITY [US-ORAL2].  
7.441: PANEL OBSERVES Part1,ChII,Sec3 DEFINES “JOINT-CRIMES” VIA 5 PROVISIONS.  
DEF: JOINT-CRIME=INTENTIONAL CRIME BY ≥2 PERSONS JOINTLY [CHN-EXH1].  
7.442: DEF: PRINCIPAL-CRIMINAL=PERSON ORGANIZES/LEADS CRIMINAL-GROUP ∨ PLAYS PRINCIPAL ROLE;  
  CRIMINAL-GROUP=STABLE ORG OF ≥3 PERSONS FOR JOINT-CRIMES;  
  RINGLEADER→PUNISHMENT BASED ON ALL GROUP-CRIMES;  
  OTHER PRINCIPAL CRIMINALS→PUNISHMENT BASED ON ALL PARTICIPATED/ORGANIZED/DIRECTED CRIMES [CHN-EXH1].
